noncompliant:
@Configuration(proxyBeanMethods = false)
class MyConfig {
  @Bean
  public ServiceA serviceA() {
    return new ServiceA();
  }
  @Bean
  public ServiceB serviceB() {
    // Noncompliant: direct call to serviceA()
    return new ServiceB(serviceA());
  }
}

compliant:
@Configuration(proxyBeanMethods = false)
class MyConfig {
  @Bean
  public ServiceA serviceA() {
    return new ServiceA();
  }
  @Bean
  public ServiceB serviceB(ServiceA serviceA) {
    // Compliant: inject ServiceA as a parameter
    return new ServiceB(serviceA);
  }
}
